SEA STRAITS

There in the horizon,
The blue breath of the sea,
The sea lions bark,
The love of salt and spray.
Roll, white cap, roll.
Carried by clandestine voices,
They ride the cresting waves,
Laughing and crashing,
Awakening the shores.

Carl Sandburg

- Carl Sandburg
